# Terraform — one interview guide (concepts + AWS + commands + layout)

**Use this file only** for Terraform prep. Pair with **`ANSIBLE_INTERVIEW_GUIDE.md`** (configure servers) and **`K8S_MANIFEST_SAMPLES.md`** (Kubernetes).

---

## 1. Terms (quick scan)

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **Provider** | Plugin for an API (AWS, Azure, …). |
| **Resource** | Create/manage cloud object (`aws_instance`, `aws_s3_bucket`). |
| **Data source** | Read-only (`data.aws_ami`, `data.aws_vpc`) — no lifecycle here. |
| **Module** | Reusable `.tf` folder with `variables` + `outputs`. |
| **State** | Maps addresses → real IDs (`terraform.tfstate`). |
| **Backend** | Where state lives (local vs **S3** + **DynamoDB** lock). |
| **Workspace** | Optional extra state files (`terraform workspace select prod`). |

**Data vs resource:** **`data`** = already exists or lookup; **`resource`** = Terraform owns create/update/delete.

