## 7. Folder structure (typical org repo)

```text
terraform/
├── main.tf
├── main-backend.tf          # optional: only backend {} block
├── provider.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
├── modules/
│   ├── vpc/                 # main.tf, variables.tf, outputs.tf
│   ├── ec2-direct/
│   ├── ec2-jumpbox/
│   ├── ecs/
│   ├── eks/                 # + node groups, IAM roles
│   ├── elasticache/
│   └── rds/
└── environments/
    ├── dev/                 # backend.tf, terraform.tfvars
    ├── prod/
    └── countries/
        ├── in-prod/
        └── us-prod/
```

**Talk track:** root **wires modules**; **dev/prod/countries** use different **S3 state keys**; **VPC outputs** feed EKS/RDS/ElastiCache; **EKS module** sets cluster + **node IAM** (worker node policies, CNI, ECR pull).

**EKS variables (typical):** `cluster_version`, `subnet_ids`, `endpoint_public_access`, node `instance_types` / `desired_size`, IAM for cluster + node group.

